The evidence with the title 'Who rules america: wealth, Income, And Power ' says The answer: not by much, if we count all of the taxes that people pay, from sales taxes to property taxes to payroll taxes ( in other words, not just income taxes). And the top 1 % of income earners actually pay a smaller percentage of their incomes to taxes than the 9 % just below them. These findings are discussed in detail  ... 
